   "overall": "CP-OFDM as a NEW modem is a SIDEGRADE-or-worse on this channel: the d2x rect128_skip64 receiver already has the CP property (grid carriers are 128-periodic; CP=128 smp), so the only deltas are coherence, shorter CP, or denser bins. Coherent detection's upper-bound gain is median 1.04 deg because additive noise is only 14.9% (median) of the measured error variance -- the budget is flutter-residual/ISI/IMD, which coherence does not touch. Shorter CP (row B, +33% gross) is KILLED by the measured reverb tail (guard-64 tail/direct -5.0 dB vs -9.3 dB at guard-128). Dense bins (row C) are KILLED by untracked flutter ICI. Bulk framing (row D, same PHY, 1.17-1.74x wall-clock) dominates every OFDM rebuild on cost and risk."
